-- Capital Research Boosts UniCredit Stake to Become Second-Biggest Investor
-- B y   S o n i a   S i r l e t t i
-- 2012-01-24T19:27:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/capital-research-boosts-unicredit-stake-to-become-second-biggest-investor.html
 Capital Research & Management Co.,
a Los Angeles-based investment fund, increased its stake in
 UniCredit SpA (UCG)  as  Italy ’s biggest bank raises cash to plug a
capital shortfall and comply with European rules.  Closely held Capital Research boosted its stake to 5.4
percent from about 2.5 percent, Italian market regulator Consob
said today in a  statement .  Capital Research becomes UniCredit’s second-biggest
investor after Abu Dhabi-based sovereign wealth fund Aabar
Investments PJSC. Aabar holds about 6.05 percent of UniCredit,
according to Consob. Aabar said on Jan. 17 that it plans to
raise its holding in the bank to 6.5 percent.  UniCredit, based in Milan, is raising 7.5 billion euros
($9.8 billion) through a rights offering. Chief Executive
Officer  Federico Ghizzoni  is also cutting costs and reducing
staff to boost profitability.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sonia Sirletti in Milan at 
 ssirletti@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net  